  "title": "Formatting imported data",
  "body": "Hi, I'm a complete newbie to Algolia but loving what I see so far.  I have a simple faceted search working for 4000 products but I have an issue where the price is being displayed in alphabetical order, not numerical.  I understand this is because the price index is a string and not an integer.\n\nI've used the instructions here: https://www.algolia.com/doc/guides/indexing/import-synchronize-data/php to import my data but am really struggling on how to tell the API to import my price field as an integer.\n\nAny help would be much appreciated.  Thanks.\n",
